Asian Firecracker Party Mix
  --Cook's Country

5 c rice chex cereal
2 c sesame sticks
1 c wasabi peas
1 c chow mein noodles
1 c honey roasted peanuts
6 tbsp unsalted butter, melted
2 tbsp shoyu
1 tsp ground ginger
3/4 tsp garlic powder
1/4 tsp cayenne

Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat to 250F. Combine cereal, sesame sticks, wasabi peas, noodles, and peanuts in large bowl. Whisk butter and shoyu in small bowl, then drizzle over cereal mixture. Sprinkle evenly with ginger, garlic powder, and cayenne and toss until well combined. Spread mixture over rimmed baking sheet and bake, stirring every 15 min, until golden and crisp, ~45 min. Cool to room temp. Serve. Can be stored in airtight container at room temp for up to 1 week. Makes ~10 c.
